<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="81" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="81">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="81">
&quot;Sterilissimus salsuginosis deserti editi Tschujae&quot;, [1800-3000 m], July 1832, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="81">A. Bunge</emphasis>
(lectotype, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="Botaniceski Zurnal (Moscow &amp; Leningrad)" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" refId="B67" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1976. Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1-788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" title="Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1 - 788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" year="1976">Tzvelev 1976</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 480, and marked in herbarium: LE! [Trinius herbarium microform image 424-A4! p.p. Bunge 1832]; isolectotypes: LE [3 specimens: TRIN-2620.01! with original description (Trinius herbarium microform 312-A1), Trinius herbarium microform images 424-A3!, 424-A5!], K [K000789849 image!; specimen labelled &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trin" authorityYear="1835" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aira altaica" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altaica">Aira altaica</taxonomicName>
Trin. Altai&quot;, &quot;Acad. St. Petrop, mis. 8br 1835&quot; is a good match for LE type material]). See 
<bibRefCitation author="Soreng, RJ" journalOrPublisher="IDC BT-" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 66" refId="B55" refString="Soreng, RJ, Peterson, PM, Annable, CR, 1995. Trinius Herbarium, Komarov Botanical Institute, St. Petersberg (Guide to the microform collection). IDC BT- 16: 1 - 66" title="Trinius Herbarium, Komarov Botanical Institute, St. Petersberg (Guide to the microform collection)." volume="16" year="1995">Soreng et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
for explanation of Trinius herbarium citations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="81" type="distribution">
